WEBVTT

00:24.685 --> 00:29.685
<font color="#ffff00">Provided by explosiveskull</font>
https://twitter.com/kaboomskull

00:51.125 --> 00:52.526
All right,
everyone out to bed.

00:52.659 --> 00:54.727
Come on, leave everything.

02:57.818 --> 03:00.520
Right. Time for bed.

03:00.653 --> 03:02.656
I'm not tired.

03:02.788 --> 03:05.191
Well, they look like
very heavy eyes to me.

03:05.325 --> 03:06.859
I'm not!

03:06.993 --> 03:09.629
So how do you explain that
little sleep-talking fiasco

03:09.763 --> 03:11.265
at dinner, hmm?

03:11.397 --> 03:12.365
My body's tired,

03:12.498 --> 03:14.000
but my mind's awake.

03:14.133 --> 03:14.967
Hmm.

03:15.102 --> 03:16.536
Well, that's one very big mind

03:16.669 --> 03:18.905
for one very tiny little girl.

03:19.038 --> 03:21.106
Will you tell me
a bedtime story?

03:21.241 --> 03:22.142
Please?

03:23.409 --> 03:26.645
You've been out all day
and it's very late!

03:26.780 --> 03:29.449
But I'm not tired. Please!

03:29.582 --> 03:30.516
You promised.

03:34.055 --> 03:38.359
How is it that when you barely
can keep your eyes open,

03:38.491 --> 03:42.929
the second you get into bed,
you're wide awake?

03:43.062 --> 03:45.598
It's called
psychological insomnia.

03:45.733 --> 03:46.667
Oh.

03:46.800 --> 03:48.435
When did you get to be so smart?

03:48.568 --> 03:50.871
I get it from you.

03:53.606 --> 03:55.109
All right,

03:55.241 --> 03:57.409
but only because
you're my favorite grandchild.

03:57.544 --> 03:59.445
I'm your only grandchild.

04:16.228 --> 04:18.899
And who is this story about,
Iris?

04:24.538 --> 04:26.072
Ballerinas.

04:32.512 --> 04:34.179
Red.

04:36.716 --> 04:37.983
Blue.

04:40.220 --> 04:42.989
Green.

04:43.122 --> 04:45.925
Orange.

04:46.060 --> 04:47.593
Indigo.

04:47.728 --> 04:49.995
Violet.

04:50.129 --> 04:51.430
Yellow.

05:13.052 --> 05:14.221
Once upon a time,

05:14.355 --> 05:17.658
in a distant world
far, far away,

05:17.790 --> 05:21.293
there was
a magical crystal kingdom.

05:54.261 --> 05:57.364
They were all wonderful dancers

05:57.497 --> 06:01.935
and their colors
were bold and bright,

06:02.069 --> 06:05.872
and they spent their days
playing and laughing

06:06.005 --> 06:07.306
and having fun.

06:07.439 --> 06:09.209
It was a magical place
where they could do

06:09.343 --> 06:13.680
their most favorite thing
of all time: dance.

06:33.966 --> 06:36.735
However...

06:36.870 --> 06:39.305
there was an evil queen.

06:41.074 --> 06:46.379
The evil queen of darkness.

07:08.634 --> 07:11.170
Gran, she sounds creepy.

07:16.076 --> 07:18.512
Silently...

07:18.644 --> 07:22.314
she plotted a way
to take over their kingdom.

07:22.449 --> 07:26.752
She was so powerful
that she could writ the colors

07:26.887 --> 07:29.689
of all their happiness.

07:36.497 --> 07:38.966
But remember,

07:39.098 --> 07:41.935
wherever there is darkness,

07:42.067 --> 07:46.271
there is always light.

07:48.007 --> 07:49.408
Oh!

08:00.786 --> 08:02.221
So what are these?

08:02.355 --> 08:03.757
Coenzyme with every meal,

08:03.889 --> 08:06.659
and arjun three times a day
for heart function,

08:06.793 --> 08:08.929
hawthorn,
the heart healthy herb,

08:09.062 --> 08:11.965
and this is spirulina.

08:13.199 --> 08:14.600
Set up a chemist at this rate.

08:14.733 --> 08:16.769
Uh, I'll drop a checklist
so we can keep track.

08:16.903 --> 08:18.272
Yeah, that'd be great.

08:18.404 --> 08:20.072
The inhibitors, propranolol,
and blood thinners

08:20.206 --> 08:21.641
we absolutely cannot forget.

08:21.774 --> 08:24.076
Maybe underline those
or put them in red?

08:29.949 --> 08:31.183
Drink up.

08:32.519 --> 08:35.721
Six, seven, eight.

08:35.855 --> 08:37.222
♪ Check, check, check, check ♪

08:53.673 --> 08:56.543
♪ I watched you walk
while you were sleepin' ♪

08:56.676 --> 08:58.345
- Iris is upstairs.
- Thanks, Mrs. Edwards!

08:58.479 --> 09:00.913
- Wash your hands, please!
- Yeah!

09:01.048 --> 09:01.980
- Good morning.
- Hi.

09:02.115 --> 09:02.950
Some letters.

09:03.082 --> 09:04.416
Great, thanks, great.

09:04.551 --> 09:05.985
♪ Sleep talk, oh,
what's your secret ♪

09:06.120 --> 09:07.754
♪ Rubber lips,
oh, preacher, preacher ♪

09:07.886 --> 09:10.022
♪ Wake, wake-up call ♪

09:10.155 --> 09:11.524
Iris, you've gotta see thi...

09:11.658 --> 09:13.092
♪ Whoa, oh, oh ♪

09:13.225 --> 09:14.495
♪ You kissed her
while the sun is cree... ♪

09:14.628 --> 09:16.062
Iris.

09:17.263 --> 09:18.865
Don't creep up on me like that.

09:18.999 --> 09:21.201
Huh! Check this out.

09:22.769 --> 09:23.736
Cool!

09:23.870 --> 09:26.072
Do they actually work?

09:26.206 --> 09:27.807
I don't like your shoes.

09:27.941 --> 09:29.209
Hey!

09:29.341 --> 09:30.943
What? There's no better way
to tell you.

09:31.076 --> 09:32.745
You wear them all the time.

09:32.879 --> 09:33.913
Mom likes them.

09:34.047 --> 09:35.215
An outfit's like a diary.

09:35.349 --> 09:37.684
It says everything
about yourself.

09:37.817 --> 09:39.218
What does mine say to you?

09:39.351 --> 09:41.454
That you like yellow.

09:42.621 --> 09:45.724
Elegance, grace.

09:45.859 --> 09:47.127
Clearly, when I grow up,

09:47.260 --> 09:50.129
I'm going to be as big
as Anna Pavlova.

09:52.032 --> 09:53.533
Who?

09:53.667 --> 09:54.401
The ballerina.

09:54.534 --> 09:55.867
You know this.

09:56.001 --> 09:59.605
Do I really have to go through
our ballet history again?

10:01.474 --> 10:03.643
She was the greatest dancer
in the world.

10:03.775 --> 10:05.778
Now, I'm going to be
as big as her one day.

10:05.913 --> 10:07.346
I'm joining The Royal Ballet,

10:07.480 --> 10:10.082
and I'm going to perform
for real kings and queens.

10:10.216 --> 10:11.585
That sounds serious.

10:11.717 --> 10:12.552
How do you join?

10:12.686 --> 10:13.653
You don't join, silly.

10:13.785 --> 10:14.920
You get picked.

10:15.054 --> 10:16.255
That's why
I have to be the best.

10:16.389 --> 10:18.290
You can help me, if you like.

10:18.424 --> 10:20.359
Okay, what do I do?

10:20.494 --> 10:22.829
Stand here,
put your hands here,

10:22.962 --> 10:24.463
and lift me up on three.

10:24.596 --> 10:27.134
One, two...

10:29.034 --> 10:30.269
On second thought,

10:30.403 --> 10:32.971
Mom always said
I have two left feet.

10:33.105 --> 10:34.640
Suit yourself.

10:34.774 --> 10:36.143
I can't stay, anyways.

10:36.275 --> 10:39.379
I just wanted to show you
the walkie-talkies.

10:43.283 --> 10:46.919
Hey, Iris,
if you do join The Royal Ballet,

10:47.052 --> 10:48.355
will you still live at home?

10:48.489 --> 10:51.591
No. I'll have to live
with the other dancers.

10:53.158 --> 10:54.427
You can come to all my shows

10:54.561 --> 10:56.196
and send me flowers
to my dressing room,

10:56.328 --> 10:57.563
if you like.

10:57.697 --> 10:58.865
I'll let you backstage.

10:58.998 --> 11:00.300
Okay.

11:03.101 --> 11:04.603
Bye, Mrs. Edwards!

11:04.738 --> 11:05.872
♪ You kissed her ♪
while the sun is creeping ♪

11:06.004 --> 11:09.241
♪ Wake, wake-up call ♪

11:09.375 --> 11:10.809
♪ Whoa, oh, oh ♪

11:10.943 --> 11:12.177
♪ You kissed her
while the sun is creeping ♪

11:12.312 --> 11:14.581
Oh, thank you.

11:14.715 --> 11:16.416
♪ Hit the clock,
it kept on beeping ♪

11:16.548 --> 11:17.617
Look.

11:17.750 --> 11:18.617
♪ Ain't got no time
for breathing ♪

11:18.750 --> 11:19.819
Do I look okay?

11:19.952 --> 11:21.120
♪ Shook you,
but you never even ♪

11:21.254 --> 11:22.622
♪ Whoa, oh, oh ♪

11:22.754 --> 11:24.057
♪ Tangerine hands,
lemon squeezer ♪

11:24.190 --> 11:26.326
- Penguin?
- Yeah, penguin team.

11:26.458 --> 11:28.694
Daddy's gotta go.

11:28.827 --> 11:29.829
Come on, scooch.

11:29.962 --> 11:32.698
♪ Wake, wake-up call ♪

11:32.832 --> 11:34.300
Night-night, Daddy.

11:34.433 --> 11:35.901
Good night, daughter.

11:37.104 --> 11:39.906
See you later.

11:44.110 --> 11:44.945
Oh!

11:46.212 --> 11:47.746
Oh, I swear...

11:47.880 --> 11:51.784
if I step on another one
of these flipping penguins...

11:56.556 --> 11:59.359
And that is why I married you.

12:07.200 --> 12:09.703
Ooh, don't mind me.

12:09.836 --> 12:11.538
It was hanging
on the bathroom door.

12:11.672 --> 12:13.907
Think you need to be on
the espresso martinis tonight.

12:14.039 --> 12:15.140
I look that bad?

12:15.274 --> 12:17.177
Double strength.

12:19.011 --> 12:20.078
I mean, I don't know.

12:20.212 --> 12:21.714
Look, maybe
we shouldn't go tonight.

12:21.849 --> 12:23.984
I need to be back on the farm
at 5:00 in the morning.

12:24.116 --> 12:25.250
They're your friends, not mine.

12:25.384 --> 12:28.688
Oh, I'm here with Iris.

12:28.822 --> 12:31.191
Go, enjoy yourselves!

12:31.323 --> 12:33.793
When was the last time
you two went out?

12:33.927 --> 12:34.995
She does have a point.

12:35.128 --> 12:36.797
We'll be three hours, tops.

12:36.929 --> 12:39.565
So mine and James's numbers
are on your phone.

12:39.700 --> 12:41.334
Do you remember
how to find contacts?

12:41.467 --> 12:44.170
I can show you again,
if you want.

12:44.303 --> 12:46.807
Here's them written down,
just in case.

12:46.940 --> 12:50.610
Also, these are the neighbors,
and this is the couple

12:50.743 --> 12:52.646
across the road that keep
putting stuff in our bins.

12:54.047 --> 12:55.748
I'm so gonna catch them one day.

12:55.881 --> 12:57.750
Don't call them
before you try Sarah.

12:57.884 --> 12:59.519
She's the one up the road,
you know,

12:59.652 --> 13:01.153
the one whose brother's
a doctor.

13:01.288 --> 13:05.392
And worst comes to worst,
this is Ian, and he's a vet.

13:05.524 --> 13:08.193
Dogs, humans, same thing, right?

13:08.327 --> 13:09.862
But call me
if you need anything.

13:09.996 --> 13:12.798
My phone's on loud all night.

13:12.932 --> 13:15.000
Remember,
just one scoop of the pink.

13:15.134 --> 13:16.369
Best do it yourself.

13:16.503 --> 13:18.104
Saying no is like saying yes
with her.

13:18.236 --> 13:20.372
Hmm, like mother, like daughter.

13:20.505 --> 13:22.475
Just don't be lenient, okay?

13:22.609 --> 13:24.944
Lights out at 7:00,
even if she doesn't wanna sleep,

13:25.077 --> 13:26.178
she needs the rest.

13:26.312 --> 13:27.547
Oh, I'm gonna fall asleep

13:27.681 --> 13:29.215
by the time
this conversation's over.

13:29.349 --> 13:30.817
Oh, just go already!

13:30.950 --> 13:32.451
And call us.

13:58.879 --> 14:02.014
Point your toes more
as you spin.

14:02.148 --> 14:03.783
Mmh-mm, and once more,

14:03.916 --> 14:05.719
or Gran'll have to show you
how it's done.

14:05.851 --> 14:09.355
Be careful, Gran,
you're really old.

14:12.292 --> 14:14.827
And third position.

14:14.961 --> 14:16.629
And fifth.

14:16.763 --> 14:17.931
And hold it.

14:18.063 --> 14:21.367
Hold it, hold it!

14:32.477 --> 14:34.680
What was it like?

14:34.813 --> 14:35.881
What's that?

14:36.014 --> 14:37.116
Being a dancer.

14:37.250 --> 14:40.219
What was it like?

14:40.352 --> 14:43.889
Well, as you said,
I'm a dinosaur,

14:44.023 --> 14:46.826
so, honestly, I don't really
remember anything.

14:46.958 --> 14:49.828
Hmm, fair enough.

14:55.634 --> 14:59.605
I didn't really fit in anywhere
when I was your age.

14:59.739 --> 15:02.075
I was actually pretty shy.

15:02.207 --> 15:03.709
You, shy?

15:04.644 --> 15:07.179
Hard to believe I know.

15:07.312 --> 15:09.848
But one day,

15:09.982 --> 15:12.551
I was given a pair
of smelly old

15:12.686 --> 15:16.122
secondhand ballet shoes.

15:16.254 --> 15:19.091
- Ew.
- Oh, no.

15:19.225 --> 15:21.360
Best present ever.

15:21.494 --> 15:24.029
'Cause when I put them on

15:24.163 --> 15:26.765
and the music would start,

15:26.899 --> 15:32.237
it was like
whatever I was doing,

15:32.371 --> 15:36.208
I was confident and brave.

15:36.341 --> 15:39.611
I could be anyone I wanted.

15:39.745 --> 15:44.317
Like the shoes were magic.

15:44.451 --> 15:46.284
Wow.

15:46.418 --> 15:49.187
I worked very hard
to be a dancer.

15:49.322 --> 15:53.592
On my point, my posture,
my strength.

15:53.725 --> 15:56.495
You have to be very strong
to be a dancer.

15:56.629 --> 16:00.633
Imagine a string
pulling you right the way up

16:00.765 --> 16:02.868
through the center of your body.

16:03.001 --> 16:04.235
That's it.

16:04.370 --> 16:06.172
That's it.
Hold it.

16:06.306 --> 16:08.908
Hold it.

16:09.042 --> 16:10.176
Keep it there,

16:10.309 --> 16:13.813
no matter what happens.

16:15.081 --> 16:17.015
Like... like what?

16:20.419 --> 16:21.286
Gran, stop it.

16:21.421 --> 16:23.156
Posture, Iris, posture!

16:27.159 --> 16:28.427
You'll sleep well tonight.

16:28.561 --> 16:32.197
Can you finish the story
about the colors?

16:33.600 --> 16:35.100
Okay, where were we?

16:35.235 --> 16:37.570
They were happy
and they were dancing,

16:37.702 --> 16:41.006
and then darkness came
to ruin everything.

16:41.140 --> 16:42.507
That's right.

16:42.642 --> 16:44.711
Party pooper.

16:44.844 --> 16:48.347
I don't like her very much.

16:48.480 --> 16:51.384
No.

16:51.517 --> 16:53.386
Me neither.

16:56.789 --> 17:01.026
The dancers' world
had been very happy,

17:01.160 --> 17:04.163
but when darkness came,

17:04.297 --> 17:07.133
she brought with her shadows

17:07.267 --> 17:10.537
that were like no other.

17:16.909 --> 17:19.679
The shadows hung
over the kingdom

17:19.810 --> 17:22.647
like a dark cloud,

17:22.781 --> 17:26.086
following the colors
wherever they went.

17:26.219 --> 17:27.721
Colors tried to ignore them,

17:27.854 --> 17:31.356
they tried to carry on dancing,
having fun,

17:31.490 --> 17:34.759
but the shadows
were always there.

17:34.894 --> 17:36.730
Wherever they turned,
wherever they looked,

17:36.863 --> 17:41.101
there they were,
draining them...

17:42.669 --> 17:45.905
...of their color
and their happiness.

17:48.507 --> 17:52.245
Colors couldn't fight back,

17:52.378 --> 17:54.079
and gradually,

17:54.213 --> 17:59.117
their radiant colors
began to fade

17:59.250 --> 18:02.421
as they lost hope.

18:02.555 --> 18:05.858
The kingdom grew
darker and darker,

18:05.991 --> 18:09.361
the colors, duller and duller,

18:09.494 --> 18:15.166
until all that was left
was black.

18:33.385 --> 18:34.319
- Hi.
- Hi.

18:34.453 --> 18:37.223
She's in the living room.

18:47.467 --> 18:50.169
That's great.

18:50.303 --> 18:52.272
And we're all done.

18:56.742 --> 18:58.979
Can we have a quick word?

19:08.320 --> 19:11.257
Have you talked to Iris
about transplant?

19:12.557 --> 19:15.528
Um, we're not there yet, are we?

19:15.662 --> 19:17.963
Surely, there's
something else first.

19:18.097 --> 19:20.365
It was never definite, was it?

19:20.500 --> 19:21.867
With cardiomyopathy,

19:22.000 --> 19:24.002
we need the thinners
to do their job.

19:24.136 --> 19:25.238
They haven't.

19:25.371 --> 19:27.774
So heart function
has deteriorated significantly.

19:27.906 --> 19:29.541
The next step would be
to contact the cardio team

19:29.674 --> 19:34.280
and discuss Iris being added
to the list for a donor heart.

19:36.281 --> 19:37.483
You're serious.

19:37.616 --> 19:39.518
Be a case of waiting,
keeping busy,

19:39.652 --> 19:41.421
makin' the most,
having fun

19:41.554 --> 19:43.490
when she feels well enough.

19:43.623 --> 19:48.394
But she will get a heart,
won't she?

19:48.528 --> 19:50.063
How many are on the list?

19:50.195 --> 19:51.763
There are usually
around 40 children in the UK

19:51.897 --> 19:53.899
waiting for hearts
at any one time.

19:54.034 --> 19:56.001
Each child needs a heart
that's the right size,

19:56.134 --> 19:58.770
and in Iris' case,
blood type, too.

19:58.903 --> 20:00.405
Child donors are rare,

20:00.538 --> 20:03.509
mainly because parents
never imagine losing a child.

20:03.642 --> 20:04.943
They don't think about donation

20:05.076 --> 20:07.813
or consider it
if the worst should happen.

20:07.946 --> 20:11.116
How long is
she gonna have to wait?

20:11.250 --> 20:12.250
For an O-negative child,

20:12.384 --> 20:15.422
statistically,
if nothing changes,

20:15.555 --> 20:19.692
you could be looking
at around 13 to 16 months.

20:19.826 --> 20:21.861
I really am very sorry.

20:57.096 --> 20:58.663
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪

20:58.797 --> 21:01.634
♪ And we spin and we leap ♪

21:01.767 --> 21:03.469
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪

21:03.603 --> 21:06.404
♪ Doo, doo, doo, doo, doo, doo,
doo, doo, doo ♪

21:07.673 --> 21:09.208
I landed my turn!

21:09.342 --> 21:12.612
Mommy, Daddy, look,
I can do my turn!

21:14.346 --> 21:16.816
Well, Polly,
it's nearly time for dinner.

21:16.949 --> 21:20.451
No, I wanna dance around
like this.

21:20.586 --> 21:22.221
♪ La, la, la ♪

21:22.354 --> 21:23.623
Silly Polly.

21:23.756 --> 21:28.261
You do know you can't dance
if you need a new heart.

21:41.874 --> 21:44.210
Polly will find a way.

21:54.720 --> 21:57.222
The heart pumps red blood cells,

21:57.355 --> 22:02.228
taking oxygen
to all of these organs here.

22:04.262 --> 22:06.965
You forgot about food and water.

22:07.099 --> 22:08.067
Hm?

22:08.201 --> 22:09.701
The heart also pumps
food and water

22:09.835 --> 22:12.105
to the organs,
the white blood cells,

22:12.238 --> 22:14.974
platelets, and plasma
to protect the body.

22:16.474 --> 22:18.043
Right.

22:18.176 --> 22:18.843
Right!

22:18.978 --> 22:20.580
Get to the point, Daddy.

22:20.712 --> 22:23.449
Yes, um...

22:23.582 --> 22:27.186
I'm afraid you can't
run around anymore, Iris.

22:27.318 --> 22:30.088
Not until you get
a new one of these

22:30.222 --> 22:37.096
and then all of these can get
a lot more... stuff again,

22:37.229 --> 22:38.364
okay?

22:38.498 --> 22:40.099
It's too risky, darling.

22:40.231 --> 22:43.301
We need you to be extra careful
from now on,

22:43.434 --> 22:47.139
that's why you can't dance
anymore, either.

22:47.272 --> 22:48.507
Okay.

22:48.641 --> 22:50.343
You sure?

22:50.476 --> 22:51.578
Mm-hm.

22:51.711 --> 22:55.280
- Any questions, or...
- Mm, no.

22:55.413 --> 22:58.917
Thanks, Daddy,
that was really interesting.

23:05.692 --> 23:07.593
I think that went pretty well.

23:07.726 --> 23:08.861
Yeah.

23:08.993 --> 23:12.263
Well done, I think she got that.

23:12.397 --> 23:14.533
- Hon, what's a platelet?
- I have no idea.

23:30.249 --> 23:30.915
Mm-hm.

23:31.049 --> 23:32.550
Yeah. No... no.

23:32.684 --> 23:33.418
Uh...

23:34.586 --> 23:35.753
I hear what you're saying,

23:35.887 --> 23:37.889
but I'm just not
understanding it.

23:38.023 --> 23:39.591
No, no, because...
Hey, Rick.

