26:24.056 --> 26:25.024
Totally hopeless.

26:25.157 --> 26:28.293
Ziggy, Merrill, Fifi, Louis...

26:28.426 --> 26:31.363
Ziggy, Merrill, Fifi, Louis.

26:32.931 --> 26:34.667
Polly?

26:37.603 --> 26:38.738
Polly?

26:51.416 --> 26:52.651
Polly!

26:52.785 --> 26:55.787
Polly.

27:01.559 --> 27:04.195
So only three of them
would be a match.

27:04.329 --> 27:07.466
Is there anything positive
or useful you wanna say?

27:09.902 --> 27:11.370
Like what?

27:11.502 --> 27:13.772
A solution, what we can do,
that we'll be all right,

27:13.905 --> 27:16.875
that we've got enough money,
we can afford it.

27:17.009 --> 27:18.477
Anything would be great.

27:20.179 --> 27:21.713
I'm just looking at the facts.

27:21.846 --> 27:23.415
What'd you want me to do?

27:23.548 --> 27:26.451
Well, sounds like the facts
don't look too good, do they?

27:58.750 --> 28:02.788
I've got pink milk.

28:06.724 --> 28:08.060
Oh!

28:09.929 --> 28:13.266
I've got a sleepy Iris today,
have I?

28:16.367 --> 28:19.303
Oh, what a shame.

28:19.438 --> 28:23.476
All these biscuits
going to waste.

28:26.111 --> 28:28.848
Double chocolate.

28:47.599 --> 28:50.401
To the rainbow of colors,

28:50.536 --> 28:56.976
it felt like darkness had
taken over their whole world.

28:57.109 --> 28:59.944
They wanted to dance
and be happy

29:00.077 --> 29:04.281
like they were before.

29:04.415 --> 29:07.251
What could they do?

29:07.385 --> 29:09.555
Was there any hope?

29:23.535 --> 29:25.971
Oh, but there was.

29:28.441 --> 29:32.545
The colors had one more weapon

29:32.678 --> 29:34.413
that they could use to fight

29:34.546 --> 29:38.049
against darkness
and her shadows,

29:38.183 --> 29:44.588
and this last weapon was
the most powerful one of all.

29:46.592 --> 29:51.630
Just when things were
at their darkest,

29:51.762 --> 29:58.102
the colors found something
deep within themselves

29:58.237 --> 30:02.641
they didn't even know existed.

30:02.773 --> 30:06.077
A secret power.

30:06.211 --> 30:08.713
An energy.

30:08.846 --> 30:11.416
A belief.

30:11.549 --> 30:17.388
And using all the strength
that they had left,

30:17.521 --> 30:22.127
they imagined a future

30:22.260 --> 30:26.030
where they had defeated
the evil queen

30:26.164 --> 30:28.567
and the kingdom was happy

30:28.700 --> 30:32.203
and they were dancing again.

30:32.336 --> 30:35.740
And they put all this energy

30:35.874 --> 30:40.078
into a little ball of light,
and...

30:42.214 --> 30:45.550
...sent it out
into the darkness.

30:45.683 --> 30:47.185
And the little ball of light

30:47.318 --> 30:49.221
floated around the darkness,

30:49.354 --> 30:53.124
illuminating a path as it went.

30:53.258 --> 30:57.763
First, it was really tiny,

30:57.895 --> 31:00.965
barely noticeable.

31:01.099 --> 31:03.801
But the colors kept hoping

31:03.935 --> 31:05.569
and believing

31:05.703 --> 31:07.806
that things would get better,

31:07.939 --> 31:09.774
and as they did,

31:09.907 --> 31:13.544
the ball of light
started to grow

31:13.679 --> 31:15.748
and become brighter,

31:15.881 --> 31:23.522
until it turned into
a dazzling white light!

31:23.655 --> 31:26.759
And light danced with darkness

31:26.892 --> 31:30.596
and brought joy
back into the world.

31:30.730 --> 31:37.368
Their radiant colors
started to return,

31:37.502 --> 31:39.538
and before she knew it,

31:39.671 --> 31:42.407
darkness was overcome
by the light,

31:42.539 --> 31:43.741
and she shattered

31:43.875 --> 31:47.077
into a million
dazzling white fragments

31:47.211 --> 31:49.013
and was defeated forever.

31:57.021 --> 32:00.024
And then light rose up
into the sky

32:00.159 --> 32:02.994
and became a radiant star.

32:07.566 --> 32:12.203
And the colors looked up
at the star

32:12.337 --> 32:15.240
and they remembered

32:15.374 --> 32:17.809
that if the spirits
of darkness

32:17.942 --> 32:22.347
ever tried to take over
their kingdom again,

32:22.480 --> 32:28.186
no matter how dark
things had become,

32:28.319 --> 32:33.023
there would always be light.

32:37.563 --> 32:39.932
They really defeated her?

32:40.065 --> 32:41.901
They did.

32:57.015 --> 33:00.052
I found this little stowaway,
by the way.

33:00.184 --> 33:01.953
Polly.

33:07.625 --> 33:10.929
You had a chat to your parents
the other day.

33:11.063 --> 33:14.466
Wanna talk about it?

33:14.598 --> 33:16.067
Can I be frank?

33:16.201 --> 33:17.434
Sure.

33:17.568 --> 33:19.303
You're frank.

33:19.438 --> 33:22.675
Cards on the table.

33:22.807 --> 33:25.343
I know I should be upset
about it all,

33:25.477 --> 33:27.812
but honestly, I'm not really.

33:27.945 --> 33:29.413
No?

33:29.548 --> 33:32.050
The thing is,
if I can't dance,

33:32.183 --> 33:34.618
I'm never gonna be a ballerina.

33:34.752 --> 33:36.355
So what you'll have to do

33:36.489 --> 33:40.259
is have a very, very clear
picture of that in your mind

33:40.392 --> 33:44.062
and never, ever deviate from it.

33:44.195 --> 33:47.799
See it, believe it,

33:47.932 --> 33:54.239
and then with all your power,
you send your wish...

33:55.507 --> 33:57.909
...out into the universe,

33:58.042 --> 34:03.948
with total conviction
that it will come true.

34:04.082 --> 34:06.552
And it will.

34:19.797 --> 34:22.933
I wish I could be a ballerina.

35:21.492 --> 35:22.893
Hey, Audrey, I...

35:26.231 --> 35:28.366
Audrey, hey.

35:31.503 --> 35:32.971
You know, there's
a little place in the island

35:33.105 --> 35:35.206
I'd really recommend going to

35:35.340 --> 35:38.309
if you wanna go, you know?

35:38.443 --> 35:40.111
With me.

35:57.329 --> 35:58.464
Audrey!

35:58.597 --> 36:00.098
Hey, Rick.

36:02.233 --> 36:03.468
How are you?

36:03.601 --> 36:06.338
Yeah, I'm good, thanks. You?

36:06.471 --> 36:08.139
Yeah, great.

36:08.273 --> 36:09.106
Yeah.

36:09.240 --> 36:10.576
And you?

36:10.708 --> 36:12.476
Already asked that, haven't I?
Yeah.

36:12.610 --> 36:13.644
Yeah.

36:13.777 --> 36:15.012
Um, you know, I...

36:15.146 --> 36:18.415
I really wanted
to ask you somethin'.

36:18.550 --> 36:19.918
Are you okay?

36:22.253 --> 36:23.355
It must be the coffee.

36:26.391 --> 36:29.695
You know coffee.

36:29.827 --> 36:31.295
You were gonna ask me something.

36:33.831 --> 36:36.234
Yeah. Um...

36:36.367 --> 36:39.403
How's the show goin'?

36:39.538 --> 36:40.704
Oh.

36:40.838 --> 36:42.574
Really good. Thanks.

36:42.708 --> 36:44.776
- Good.
- Yeah.

36:44.909 --> 36:48.479
- This is yours.
- Okay.

36:48.612 --> 36:50.781
- Thanks.
- Yep, yep.

36:50.916 --> 36:52.050
- Bye.
- All right.

36:52.182 --> 36:53.351
Yep, next time.

36:53.485 --> 36:54.652
Yeah.

36:54.786 --> 36:55.954
The same place next...
never mind.

36:56.088 --> 36:57.455
- Have a nice evening, Rick.
- Okay.

37:25.983 --> 37:27.384
What's it today, then?

37:27.518 --> 37:29.253
English.

37:29.387 --> 37:31.422
Oh, we did that yesterday.

37:31.556 --> 37:32.956
Maybe it's time for some maths.

37:33.090 --> 37:34.458
No!

37:34.592 --> 37:35.594
Yes, come on, you need to.

37:35.726 --> 37:37.495
