♪ On the edge ♪

01:02:51.541 --> 01:02:54.210
♪ Or deep inside ♪

01:02:54.344 --> 01:02:55.944
♪ Right upfront ♪

01:02:57.347 --> 01:03:00.417
♪ To where it likes to hide ♪

01:03:00.550 --> 01:03:05.522
♪ We only see
what we want to see ♪

01:03:06.889 --> 01:03:11.994
♪ So we don't see
much of anything ♪

01:03:22.706 --> 01:03:25.409
- Coming in.
- Go away, Gran.

01:03:25.541 --> 01:03:27.510
Well, that's not very nice.

01:03:32.949 --> 01:03:37.386
Oh, what dreadful weather!

01:03:37.519 --> 01:03:39.623
I don't feel well.

01:03:40.923 --> 01:03:42.326
Come here.

01:03:44.327 --> 01:03:47.364
Nope, no temperature.

01:03:47.496 --> 01:03:49.832
My heart hurts.

01:03:53.269 --> 01:03:55.704
Oh dear.

01:03:55.838 --> 01:04:00.777
Oh dear, dear, dear,
no, not good.

01:04:00.909 --> 01:04:03.545
Not good at all.

01:04:03.679 --> 01:04:05.013
Really?

01:04:05.148 --> 01:04:09.753
Sounds like your heart's fallen
all the way down to your tummy.

01:04:11.054 --> 01:04:12.923
Had any nice dreams lately?

01:04:13.056 --> 01:04:14.758
What's the point?

01:04:17.893 --> 01:04:20.262
Do you think the colors
would have given up?

01:04:20.396 --> 01:04:21.865
It doesn't work.

01:04:21.998 --> 01:04:23.099
It does.

01:04:23.233 --> 01:04:24.702
And how can you be so sure?

01:04:24.835 --> 01:04:26.869
I hate Mum,
she's always shoutin' at dad

01:04:27.003 --> 01:04:30.806
and she's makin' him
sleep on the sofa.

01:04:30.940 --> 01:04:31.807
Oh, darling.

01:04:33.643 --> 01:04:37.313
Mummy and Daddy
love you very much.

01:04:37.447 --> 01:04:39.182
You're a lucky girl
to have parents

01:04:39.315 --> 01:04:42.418
that love you so.

01:04:42.552 --> 01:04:45.355
The power's rubbish anyways.

01:04:45.489 --> 01:04:48.657
It absolutely isn't, Iris.

01:04:48.791 --> 01:04:50.960
Do you really think it works?

01:04:51.094 --> 01:04:53.829
I know it does.

01:04:55.864 --> 01:04:58.767
Long time ago,
there was a little girl,

01:04:58.902 --> 01:05:04.240
about your age,
and just like you right now,

01:05:04.373 --> 01:05:08.110
she had to face
some scary times.

01:05:08.244 --> 01:05:11.381
But this little girl,
she didn't have a grandma

01:05:11.514 --> 01:05:15.717
or even a mummy
that she could talk to.

01:05:15.851 --> 01:05:20.089
There was just her
and the others.

01:06:17.047 --> 01:06:18.614
All right,
everyone out of bed.

01:06:18.748 --> 01:06:20.217
Come on, leave everything.

01:06:24.186 --> 01:06:25.454
Maisie!

01:06:28.190 --> 01:06:29.393
Come on, slow poke.

01:06:29.525 --> 01:06:30.659
One, two, three,
come with me, four.

01:06:30.793 --> 01:06:32.663
All right, go on. Come on.

01:06:32.795 --> 01:06:35.064
All right, come with me,
come with me.

01:06:35.197 --> 01:06:36.298
Here we go.

01:06:36.432 --> 01:06:38.101
All right, it's gonna be fine.

01:06:42.938 --> 01:06:44.473
What about Mister Augustus?

01:06:44.608 --> 01:06:46.242
No, we don't have time!

01:06:48.445 --> 01:06:49.446
Come on.

01:06:49.579 --> 01:06:50.847
It's all right,
it's all right.

01:06:55.619 --> 01:06:57.187
Let's go.

01:07:03.559 --> 01:07:04.727
Jenny and Simon.

01:07:10.833 --> 01:07:12.535
Come on.
Jenny, come.

01:07:18.240 --> 01:07:19.242
Jenny.

01:07:19.375 --> 01:07:21.077
Simon.

01:07:21.210 --> 01:07:22.110
Here we go.

01:07:32.088 --> 01:07:33.390
Just stay here.

01:07:36.360 --> 01:07:37.961
We'll wait for the all-clear.

01:07:38.094 --> 01:07:39.061
Before you know it,

01:07:39.195 --> 01:07:41.364
we'll be curled back up
in our beds again.

01:07:43.032 --> 01:07:47.771
They all just wanted the war
to end, to be safe,

01:07:47.903 --> 01:07:51.041
to play with their brothers
and sisters again,

01:07:51.173 --> 01:07:54.543
and, of course,
she wanted to dance.

01:07:54.677 --> 01:07:58.614
There's no way
they got out alive.

01:07:58.748 --> 01:08:01.984
It got a lot worse,
believe me.

01:08:36.520 --> 01:08:38.587
They must be
right overhead, Miss.

01:08:47.296 --> 01:08:49.663
I think
they hit the power station.

01:08:51.501 --> 01:08:54.136
But if they are that close,
they'll be past us soon.

01:08:57.974 --> 01:08:59.675
The roof's going to come down!

01:09:19.795 --> 01:09:22.399
So what happened?

01:09:22.533 --> 01:09:29.171
Well, Miss Shaw
told tell them a story,

01:09:29.305 --> 01:09:34.076
a wise tale
about how the colors

01:09:34.211 --> 01:09:38.081
defeated the evil queen
of darkness.

01:09:38.212 --> 01:09:39.215
The story!

01:09:39.349 --> 01:09:40.617
Yes.

01:09:40.750 --> 01:09:41.984
And then,

01:09:42.118 --> 01:09:45.587
each one closed their eyes,

01:09:45.720 --> 01:09:48.090
took a deep breath,

01:09:48.224 --> 01:09:53.261
and imagined
the war would end,

01:09:53.395 --> 01:09:59.670
and wished
that they would be found.

01:09:59.802 --> 01:10:03.539
And they hoped,
and they prayed

01:10:03.672 --> 01:10:07.409
as hard as they could.

01:10:07.542 --> 01:10:09.512
And it was!

01:10:09.645 --> 01:10:13.715
Years later, everyone said
what miracle of the blitz

01:10:13.850 --> 01:10:16.719
it was that
they were even found!

01:10:16.853 --> 01:10:19.489
No search parties
were sent for,

01:10:19.622 --> 01:10:21.990
no instructions
were given to help them.

01:10:22.125 --> 01:10:25.494
I mean, nobody even knew
where they were.

01:10:25.628 --> 01:10:29.265
But by luck, by chance,

01:10:29.399 --> 01:10:33.670
some would say
a little bit of magic,

01:10:33.802 --> 01:10:35.904
they were found.

01:10:37.207 --> 01:10:39.508
And did the girl
ever become a dancer?

01:10:39.641 --> 01:10:41.444
Oh, yes.

01:10:41.578 --> 01:10:46.382
Many years, she performed
all over the world.

01:10:46.515 --> 01:10:47.750
In fact,

01:10:47.884 --> 01:10:50.185
her granddaughter
this very day

01:10:50.319 --> 01:10:54.222
is thinking of following
in her footsteps.

01:10:54.356 --> 01:10:55.324
Me?

01:10:55.458 --> 01:10:57.126
The girl in the story was you!

01:10:57.260 --> 01:10:58.327
Yes.

01:10:58.461 --> 01:11:00.663
So it really does work.

01:11:00.796 --> 01:11:02.297
Yes.

01:11:10.774 --> 01:11:12.575
I want you to have this.

01:11:14.342 --> 01:11:15.677
It was mine.

01:11:15.811 --> 01:11:17.814
From the orphanage?

01:11:19.949 --> 01:11:21.483
Thanks, Gran.

01:11:26.055 --> 01:11:28.524
What was it like
being in an orphanage,

01:11:28.658 --> 01:11:30.293
and not having mum and dad?

01:11:30.426 --> 01:11:32.128
Tell me some stories.

01:11:32.261 --> 01:11:35.198
I think that's enough
for one night, don't you?

01:11:35.331 --> 01:11:38.367
But, Gran,
I'm not even tired.

01:11:38.501 --> 01:11:42.806
Well, I think we'll keep them
closed just in case.

01:11:42.939 --> 01:11:45.709
I'll tell you some more stories
tomorrow night.

01:11:52.247 --> 01:11:54.283
Look at this one.
Look what the tide brought in.

01:11:54.417 --> 01:11:56.185
Oh. Here's the bucket.

01:11:56.319 --> 01:11:57.620
Now, put 'em in,
put 'em in, put 'em in.

01:11:57.753 --> 01:11:59.889
Go, go, go, go, go.

01:12:00.023 --> 01:12:01.557
Yep, now that'll go
in the bucket.

01:12:04.560 --> 01:12:05.795
Look at this one.

01:12:05.927 --> 01:12:07.095
- Oh.
- Oh, nice.

01:12:07.229 --> 01:12:08.763
Look, Iris,
you got wet shoes now.

01:12:11.835 --> 01:12:13.103
Go on, go on.

01:12:13.235 --> 01:12:14.569
No. Stop.

01:13:29.712 --> 01:13:31.314
Oh, you all right there, James?

01:13:32.948 --> 01:13:35.116
Yeah, only a couple today.

01:13:35.251 --> 01:13:36.351
Oh, if you scrub that
any harder,

01:13:36.485 --> 01:13:37.354
the paint will come off.

01:13:38.487 --> 01:13:39.822
What?

01:13:39.956 --> 01:13:41.958
Well, I... I meant the boat.

01:13:44.527 --> 01:13:45.862
Oh.

01:13:46.828 --> 01:13:48.164
Thanks.

01:13:49.497 --> 01:13:50.932
How's Iris?

01:13:54.270 --> 01:13:57.707
Yeah, uh, no, she's...
she's okay.

01:13:57.840 --> 01:14:01.377
It's her birthday next week,
so we're kinda focusing on that.

01:14:07.516 --> 01:14:09.485
If there's anything
I can do...

01:15:01.904 --> 01:15:04.040
130 over 80.

01:15:04.172 --> 01:15:06.542
110 over...

01:15:08.978 --> 01:15:11.014
...63.

01:15:16.150 --> 01:15:17.853
That's not right.

01:15:17.987 --> 01:15:20.023
I'm calling Dr. Steadman.

01:15:20.788 --> 01:15:23.792
No, Mum, I'm fine.

01:15:23.926 --> 01:15:25.360
James, I'm callin' him.

01:15:25.493 --> 01:15:27.195
Yeah.

01:15:27.329 --> 01:15:28.465
No.

01:15:29.466 --> 01:15:32.269
I wanna be home
for tomorrow.

01:15:32.402 --> 01:15:33.802
Oh, honey.

01:15:33.935 --> 01:15:36.773
Darling,
it's too much of a risk.

01:15:36.905 --> 01:15:39.307
But, daddy, it's okay.

01:15:39.442 --> 01:15:42.078
I know I'm gonna get
a new heart.

01:15:42.211 --> 01:15:44.213
Why is that?

01:15:44.346 --> 01:15:47.082
I asked the universe for one.

01:16:14.810 --> 01:16:15.912
Look at you.

01:16:16.045 --> 01:16:17.680
Foolin' around
with that stupid guitar

01:16:17.814 --> 01:16:19.815
and makin' a fool of yourself.

01:17:25.247 --> 01:17:26.615
Look at this one!

01:18:11.092 --> 01:18:12.461
Hello.

01:18:20.103 --> 01:18:22.503
Iris!

01:18:22.637 --> 01:18:24.606
Hey, sweetie.
Hey, sweetie.

01:18:24.740 --> 01:18:26.641
We're gonna make you
feel better, okay?

01:18:26.774 --> 01:18:27.643
This is it.

01:18:27.777 --> 01:18:28.978
- Come on.
- What's happening?

01:18:29.110 --> 01:18:30.778
- Come on.
- Where's Gran?

01:18:30.912 --> 01:18:31.946
Oh, you'll see her later.

01:18:32.081 --> 01:18:33.382
Come on.

01:18:33.515 --> 01:18:35.049
- Mister Augustus!
- There's no time!

01:18:35.184 --> 01:18:36.252
Come on.

01:20:15.184 --> 01:20:16.385
Hi, Rick.
Bit late, isn't it?

01:20:16.519 --> 01:20:18.020
Here, you gotta have this.

01:20:22.256 --> 01:20:25.761
This little girl, she's got...
she wants to be a ballerina.

01:20:25.895 --> 01:20:29.132
That's an entry form.
You just gotta see it, please.

01:20:30.765 --> 01:20:32.467
Okay.

01:20:32.601 --> 01:20:34.304
- You okay?
- Yeah.

01:20:35.738 --> 01:20:38.407
Do you wanna get coffee
sometime as well,

01:20:38.539 --> 01:20:39.943
with me, anytime?

01:20:43.679 --> 01:20:44.881
Sure.

01:20:48.650 --> 01:20:49.351
Goodbye.

01:20:49.484 --> 01:20:50.652
All right.

01:21:19.047 --> 01:21:20.448
It won't be long now.

01:21:20.582 --> 01:21:24.253
Just try and relax,
you're in safe hands, okay?

01:21:24.386 --> 01:21:25.554
Okay, we're ready for her.

01:21:27.489 --> 01:21:29.358
Okay, sweetie,
we have to go now.

01:21:29.490 --> 01:21:32.127
Be a good brave girl
for Mummy, okay?

01:21:32.261 --> 01:21:33.830
Where's Gran?

01:21:33.962 --> 01:21:35.163
You'll see her later.

01:21:35.297 --> 01:21:36.465
We'll be right outside.

01:21:36.599 --> 01:21:38.301
